p.m:
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
    \frac{2}{25} \div \left(-\frac{9}{20}\right)
        \amp = \frac{2}{25} \cdot \left(-\frac{20}{9}\right) \amp \hbox{We can divide the first denominator and the second numerator by 5.}\\
        \amp = \frac{2}{5 }\cdot\left(-\frac{4}{9}\right) \\
        \amp = -\frac{8}{45}
\end{aligned}
    }
